    "title": "Entry-Level Fleet Manager at Swiggy Logistics International Enterprises",
    "description": "Join the Swiggy Logistics International Enterprises family as a Fleet Manager in Aurangabad. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Swiggy Logistics International Enterprises:\nSwiggy Logistics International Enterprises is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Track shipments in real-time and resolve delivery exceptions\n• Oversee end-to-end logistics operations for timely delivery\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Conduct periodic vendor audits and evaluate logistics partners\n• Ensure proper handling, packaging, and labeling of goods\n• Coordinate with customer service teams to resolve delivery issues\n• Manage a fleet of vehicles and coordinate with drivers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in Vendor Management\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in SAP SCM\n• Proficiency in Cold Chain Logistics\n• Proficiency in Fleet Management\n• Proficiency in TMS\n• Proficiency in Last Mile Delivery\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Learning & development budget\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Swiggy Logistics International Enterprises!",
